   <div>
                Hi Sangyong,</div>
<p>We’re writing to let you know that <strong>on September 27, 2021,</strong> we will be updating the <a>Firebase Data Processing and Security Terms</a> and <a>Crashlytics and App Distribution Data Processing and Security Terms</a>.</p>

<p>As part of these changes, we will incorporate the new versions of the <a>Standard Contractual Clauses</a> (“SCCs”) approved by the European Commission on June 4, 2021. The new SCCs replace the clauses previously approved under Directive 95/46/EC.</p>

What happens next?

<p><strong>No action is required on your part</strong> to accept these updates. <strong>These updates will apply to your use of the relevant service(s) from October 27, 2021.</strong></p>
<p>
You can review more information about the new SCCs in the<a> Privacy and Security in Firebase</a> resources.
     </p>






<div>
